                <h1>Who Was the Book of Jude Written To?</h1>
                <p>The Book of Jude was written to early Christian believers, specifically intended for those facing false teachings and moral decay within their communities. It serves as a warning and encouragement to persevere in faith, urging recipients to contend for the faith and adhere to the teachings of Jesus Christ amidst challenges.</p>
